  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Changing this bug with Asheesh's permission to expand it a bit.

This bug now covers creating a new class of people called "ambassadors".  A user
can flag themselves as an ambassador for a project.  If they are marked as such,
they will be notified whenever a user clicks on the big green button for that
project.  Notification will be done by email.  The email will contain a message
about why the email was sent, a link to un-ambassador, a link to the OpenHatch
site where an email address for the user can be found, and perhaps some
suggestions on what to do with this information.

Changes that need to happen:

1. On <a href="https://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/,">https://openhatch.org/+portfolio/editor/,</a> the user will be able to click a
checkbox labeled, "I'm an ambassador for this project!".  Clicking on this
checkbox and saving the project information makes this user an ambassador for
that project.  There should be some help text available telling the user what it
means to be an ambassador.  Either that can be done by linking the word
"ambassador" or having a ? link or however it is that sort of thing happens on
OpenHatch.

2. (optional) On <a href="https://openhatch.org/people/willkahngreene/,">https://openhatch.org/people/willkahngreene/,</a> for any projects
the user is an ambassador for, text along the lines of "I am an ambassador"
should appear.

(alternative) Add a "I am an ambassador" text to the info column on the left
side that lists projects the user is an ambassador for.

3. When a user clicks on the big green button, an email is sent to all
ambassadors for that project along the lines of:

"""
Hi!

PERSON has expressed an interest in helping out with project XYZ by clicking on
the big green button.  You can contact PERSON at this link:

&lt;link to profile page&gt;

Contact PERSON and introduce yourself.  Then help PERSON get involved in project
XYZ.  &lt;insert advice here&gt;

You have elected to be an ambassador for project XYZ and that's why you're
receiving this email.  If you no longer want to be an ambassador, then
&lt;instructions here to remove ambassador flag&gt;.

Rock on!

OpenHatch - making FLOSS development rock!
"""


I think that's all that's needed.  I haven't looked at the OH code, so I have no
idea if this is doable as it stands, or needs some augmentation.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
